## About this Course
- In this course, you’ll learn how to keep track of the different versions of your code and configuration 
files using a popular version control system (VCS) called Git.
 - 1) how to setup an account with a service called GitHub so that you can create your very own remote repositories to store your code 
and configuration. 
- 2) learn about Git's core functionality so you can understand how and why it’s used in organizations.
- 3)look into both basic and more advanced features, like branches and merging. We'll demonstrate 
how having a working knowledge of a VCS like Git can be a lifesaver in emergency situations or when debugging.
 - explore how to use a VCS to work with others through remote repositories, like the ones provided by GitHub.
- 4)  store your code's history in Git and collaborate with others in GitHub, where you’ll also start creating your own portfolio! 
